        Parameters:
        url - URL that has already has already been URL encoded. Please see URL.encode(String) and URL.encodePathSegment(String) and URL.encodeQueryString(String) for how to do this.

      • setHeader

        public void setHeader(java.lang.String key,
             java.lang.String value)
               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Sets a request header with the given name and value. If a header with the specified name has already been set then the new value will be combined with previous one as comma separated list (According to section 4.2 of RFC 2616). note
        Parameters:
        key - header token
        value - header value NOTE: The empty string is legal and represents the empty header value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if header token is null or empty.
